# usePHToast replaces direct toast library imports in editors

Never import `ToastContainer` or any toast library directly in editors or apps. The host app (Connect) already provides the toast infrastructure.

```typescript
import { usePHToast } from "@powerhousedao/reactor-browser";

export default function Editor() {
  const toast = usePHToast();

  const handleSave = () => {
    toast("Document saved!", { type: "success" });
  };
}
```

Available toast types: `default`, `success`, `error`, `warning`, `info`, `connect-success`, `connect-warning`, `connect-loading`, `connect-deleted`.

Options include `autoClose` (ms or false) and `containerId` for targeting specific containers.

